urls.title: Away From Home
urls.description: The Athletic is given inside access to leading Ukrainian football club Shakhtar Donetsk as they compete against the world's best teams despite being unable to play at home - in their own stadium - due to Russia's invasion of Ukraine. The Athletic's Adam Crafton and Joey D'Urso travelled with the team to gather first-hand accounts of the extraordinary challenges in the lives of players and staff as they compete against the world's best players on the biggest stage under unprecedented, ever-changing circumstances. Episode 4, 5 & 6 coming November 14th.

urls.title: 'A total injustice': Uruguay vent fury the morning after the night before
urls.description: Uruguay players were still unhappy when The Athletic spoke to them as they departed their Qatar team base on Saturday

tweets.text:
I went to Uruguay's team hotel and spoke to some of the players about their controversial exit from the World Cup and the referee in the eye of the storm.

“For me it was a total injustice. We’re already out because of him." 
https://t.co/8Uy9y7iVxN

To those US fans who come around every 4 years…

Stick around. It would be nice to have you.

Watch MLS. Watch the Premier League, La Liga, Serie A, Ligue 1, Bundesliga. We have access to every game broadcast in all those leagues.

No better time to get into the sport than now.

urls.title: De Ligt ‘did not expect’ to be starting for Netherlands at World Cup
urls.description: Bayern Munich defender Matthijs de Ligt has said he is “okay” with not starting for the Netherlands at the 2022 World Cup because he “expected to play nothing” under Louis van Gaal in Qatar. De Ligt, 23, started the Netherlands first match at the tournament — a 2-0 victory over Senegal —...

tweets.text: 🚨 Matthijs de Ligt admits “I expected to play nothing at this World Cup” due to “the way the coach sees me in the team” so “I’ve already played more than I expected” + “I was ok with that”. Adds he was not close to joining Chelsea in summer @TheAthleticFC https://t.co/D5Mdj5r8R1
